      "content": "To effectively defend the pro-enforcement side, your students should emphasize the importance of securing the border to prevent human trafficking, protect national security, and prevent the influx of unvetted individuals who could potentially harm the economy and social services. They should also highlight the need for stricter immigration enforcement to deter would-be migrants, reduce the financial burden on taxpayers, and preserve the integrity of the US labor market. Additionally, they can argue that increased border security and enforcement will allow for more effective deportation of undocumented immigrants, reducing the strain on local law enforcement and courts.",
